Justin 闭嘴
Justin. Shut up.

192
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:46,308
不 不 不 那条路是用来迷惑人的
No, no, no, that's a decoy trail.

193
00:15:46,398 --> 00:15:47,208
他从这儿走了
He went this way.

194
00:15:47,288 --> 00:15:50,128
- 你凭什么这么说?  - 经验
- And you're basing this on what?  - Experience.

195
00:15:51,448 --> 00:15:52,118
Aldo呀
Aldo.

196
00:15:52,208 --> 00:15:53,258
干嘛?
What?

197
00:15:53,348 --> 00:15:54,848
我觉得她说对了
I think she's right.

198
00:15:55,348 --> 00:15:56,848
她当然对
Of course she is.

199
00:15:57,668 --> 00:15:58,988
请您带路 公主
After you, princess.

200
00:16:01,058 --> 00:16:03,268
你想用什么办法把男朋友带回来?
So what's your strategy for bringing you boyfriend back?

201
00:16:03,368 --> 00:16:06,228
希望你有辄 因为他出去的时候 射伤了个人
I hope you got one, because he shot a guy on his way out.

202
00:16:06,338 --> 00:16:08,528
- 他要是这么对我的话 我就把他脑袋打爆  - 喂 看着点儿
- If he tries that on me, I'm gonna blow his head off.  - Whoa. Watch it.

203
00:16:11,268 --> 00:16:12,528
谢谢
Thank you.

204
00:16:13,278 --> 00:16:14,968
看着像Rousseau的陷阱
Looks like one of Rousseau's traps.

205
00:16:15,058 --> 00:16:17,228
那法国女人? 不 她已经死了好几年了
The French woman? No, she's been dead for years.

206
00:16:17,328 --> 00:16:19,638
- 这... 这不可能是她的...  - Justin!
- This... this couldn't be one of her...  - Justin!

207
00:16:19,848 --> 00:16:21,568
闭嘴
Shut up.

208
00:16:25,108 --> 00:16:26,428
他要说什么?
What was he gonna say?

209
00:16:28,128 --> 00:16:29,748
你都不记得我了 是吗?
You don't even remember me, do you?

210
00:16:31,008 --> 00:16:32,338
你认不出我?
You don't recognize me?

211
00:16:34,398 --> 00:16:35,898
哦 可能这个会让你想起来
Well, maybe this will jog your memory.

212
00:16:36,028 --> 00:16:36,928
3年前
Three years ago,

213
00:16:37,018 --> 00:16:40,368
你上演了一出越狱 而且你是用
you staged yourself a little prison break, and you did it

214
00:16:40,448 --> 00:16:42,388
来福枪的枪托 敲晕了旁边的警卫
by knocking the guard out with the butt of you rifle.

215
00:16:42,478 --> 00:16:44,068
那个人就是我
That would be me.

216
00:16:53,958 --> 00:16:54,948
你干什么?
What are you doing?

217
00:16:58,888 --> 00:16:59,988
逃跑
Escaping.

218
00:17:07,408 --> 00:17:08,328
Sayid啊!
Sayid!

219
00:17:11,128 --> 00:17:11,898
还好吗 哥们儿?
You okay, man?

220
00:17:12,028 --> 00:17:13,828
Jack! 他回来了!
Jack! He's back!

221
00:17:20,078 --> 00:17:21,678
Sayid 发生什么事了?
Sayid, what happened?

222
00:17:22,698 --> 00:17:24,628
- 他们对我用刑  - 为什么?
- They tortured me.  - Why?

223
00:17:24,738 --> 00:17:28,568
不知道 他们什么也没问
Don't know. They didn't ask any questions.

224
00:17:37,458 --> 00:17:38,518
让开
Step aside.

225
00:17:56,228 --> 00:17:57,088
嘿 Shephard
Hey, Shephard.

226
00:17:58,638 --> 00:18:00,078
我们正盼着你自己过来
We were hoping you'd come on your own.

227
00:18:00,388 --> 00:18:02,058
你们到底对Sayid做了什么?
What the hell did you do to Sayid?

228
00:18:03,568 --> 00:18:06,828
我们... 什么都没做 你... 你朋友病了
We... we didn't do anything to him. Y... your friend is sick.

229
00:18:11,338 --> 00:18:12,188
他是...
He's...

230
00:18:12,948 --> 00:18:15,238
是的 我... 这真的不能...
Yeah, I... It's not really...

231
00:18:15,318 --> 00:18:16,808
这真的直译不了
It's not really a literal translation.

232
00:18:16,888 --> 00:18:18,728
最接近的说法是...
The closest thing would be...

233
00:18:19,628 --> 00:18:20,398
感染
infected.

234
00:18:20,498 --> 00:18:23,268
感染? 他都没有发烧
Infected? He's not even running a fever.

235
00:18:26,168 --> 00:18:26,748
什么意思...
What...

236
00:18:27,188 --> 00:18:28,858
我说了什么好笑的话吗?
Did I say something funny?

237
00:18:28,948 --> 00:18:31,878
我不这么认为 他一点幽默感都没有
I doubt it. He doesn't really have a sense of humor.

238
00:18:44,898 --> 00:18:47,408
他说 你得把这粒药给你朋友
He says you have to give your friend this pill.

239
00:18:50,178 --> 00:18:51,288
你说真的?
Are you serious?

240
00:18:53,648 --> 00:18:54,908
为什么你不自己给他?
Why don't you give it to him?

241
00:18:56,208 --> 00:18:58,398
因为只有他自己愿意吃 才有效果
Because it won't work unless he takes it willingly,

242
00:18:58,438 --> 00:19:00,358
但是由我们给他 他肯定是不情愿的
and won't take it willingly from us.

243
00:19:00,418 --> 00:19:01,938
呃 你们也许该在对他用刑之前
Well, then maybe you should've asked him to take it

244
00:19:02,058 --> 00:19:02,998
- 让他吃药  - 我们没有对他用刑
- before you tortured him.  - We didn't torture him.

245
00:19:03,088 --> 00:19:10,028
- 我们只是在为他诊断  - 看他是不是真感染了
- We were diagnosing him.  - To see if he was infected.

246
00:19:10,148 --> 00:19:11,498
是的
Yes.

247
00:19:11,978 --> 00:19:13,148
除非我知道成分
I'm not gonna give anything to Sayid

248
